definition.value: An amino oligosaccharide that is an undecasaccharide in which two tetrasaccharide branches, each formed from fucose, galactose, N-acetylglucosamine and mannose residues linked alpha(1->2), beta(1->3) and beta(1->2) respectively, are linked alpha(1->3) and alpha(1->6) to the mannose residue of a trisaccharide chain consisting of mannose and two N-acetylglucosamine residues all linked beta(1->4) with a beta-configuration of the anomeric carbon of the N-acetylglucosamine residue at the reducing end.
An organic anionic group resulting from the removal of the proton from the sulfamic acid group of [4)-D-GlcpNS-(1->] residue. The major structure at pH 7.3 of N-sulfo-D-glucosamine residue.
An organic cationic group obtained by protonation of the amino group of [4)-D-GlcpN-(1->] residue. The major structure at pH 7.3 of D-glucosamine residue.
A monosaccharide residue obtained by removal of the anomeric hydroxy group and the hydrogen attached to the 4-hydroxy group of D-glucosamine.
An organic group obtained by removal of the hydrogen attached to the nitrogen at position 1 from cytosine.
An organic group obtained by removal of the hydrogen attached to the nitrogen at position 1 from 5-methylcytosine.
A monosaccharide residue obtained by removal of the anomeric hydroxy group and the hydrogen attached to the 4-hydroxy group of N-sulfo-D-glucosamine.
alpha-L-Fucp-(1->2)-beta-D-Galp-(1->3)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-D-Glcp in which the configuration at the anomeric carbon of the glucose residue is beta.
A dihydroascorbigen hexoside in which the hexoside component is a beta-D-glucosyl residue attached at position 5 via a glycosidic bond.
A branched amino oligosaccharide comprising two fucosyl residues, three galactose residues and two N-acetylglucosamine residues, with a glucose residue at the reducing end.
An amino-acid residue derived from hexadec-2-enoyl-pantetheine-4-phosphorylserine.
An alpha-amino-acid residue cation residue derived from N(omega)-methyl-arginine.
An amino-acid residue derived from (3R)-3-hydroxypalmitoyl-pantetheine-4-phosphorylserine.
A purinyl group derived from removal of the hydrogen attached to the nitrogen at position 9 from N(6)-(dimethylallyl)adenine.
The hydrochloride salt of buprenorphine.
An amino-acid residue derived from dodecanoyl-pantetheine-4-phosphorylserine.
A primary carboxamide in which the amide linkage is bonded directly to an aliphatic system.
An alpha-amino-acid residue anion obtained by removal of a proton form the sulfate group of L-tyrosine-O-sulfate residue.
A nucleotide residue derived from cyclobutadithymidine.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 28 carbons in total with 6 double bonds.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 28 carbons in total with 5 double bonds.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 28 carbons in total with 4 double bonds.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 28 carbons in total with 3 double bonds.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 28 carbons in total with 2 double bonds.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 28 carbons in total with 1 double bond.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 28 carbons in total with 0 double bonds.
A benzoate anion formed by deprotonation of the carboxy OH group of N-alkylphthalic monoamide. Major structure at pH 7.3.
An ammonium ion derivative resulting from the protonation of the nitrogen atom of a primary amino compound. Major species at pH 7.3.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 30 carbons in total with 6 double bonds.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 30 carbons in total with 5 double bonds.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 30 carbons in total with 4 double bonds.
The hydrochloride salt of doxycycline.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 30 carbons in total with 3 double bonds.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 30 carbons in total with 2 double bonds.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 30 carbons in total with 1 double bond.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 30 carbons in total with 0 double bonds.
A peptide anion formed by deprotonation of the terminal carboxy group of N-tetradecanoylglycylpeptide. Major species at pH 7.3.
A deoxyribonucleotide residue derived from a purine deoxyribonucleotide.
A deoxyribonucleotide residue derived from a pyrimidine deoxyribonucleotide.

A corticotropin-releasing hormone from sheep composed of Ser, Gln, Glu, Pro, Pro, Ile, Ser, Leu, Asp, Leu, Val, Phe, His, Leu, Leu, Arg, Glu, Val, Leu, Glu, Met, Thr, Lys, Ala, Asp, Gln, Leu, Ala, Gln, Gln, Ala, His, Ser, Asn, Arg, Lys, Leu, Leu, Asp, Ile and Ala-NH2 residues joined in sequence.
A nitroso compound that is hydrogen sulfide in which one of the hydrogens is replaced by a nitroso group.
An alpha-amino-acid residue derived from N(omega)-methyl-arginine.

A nucleoside analogue in which the nucleobase portion is a 1,4,5,6,8-pentaazaacenaphthylene ring system substituted with an amino group at position 3, and a methyl group at position 5 and is bound to the beta-D-ribofuranosyl moiety by an N(1)-glycosidic linkage.

A family of peptide hormones derived from a 191-membered prehormone, secreted by the paraventricular nucleus (PVN) of the hypothalamus in response to stress. The first full sequence was discovered in sheep, those in rats and humans differ from the ovine sequence by 7 amino acids.

A corticotropin-releasing hormone from human/rat composed of Ser, Glu, Glu, Pro, Pro, Ile, Ser, Leu, Asp, Leu, Val, Phe, His, Leu, Leu, Arg, Glu, Val, Leu, Glu, Met, Ala, Arg, Ala, Glu, Gln, Leu, Ala, Gln, Gln, Ala, His, Ser, Asn, Arg, Lys, Leu, Met, Glu, Ile and Ile-NH2 residues joined in sequence.
A polysaccharide composed of an alpha-D-glucosyl residue joined to a [(2->6)-beta-D-fructosyl]n moiety by an alpha-(1->2) linkage.
An organic anionic group arising from the deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of pseudouridine 5'-phosphate residue.
